\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/group.z_group}{Z-group}}
\begin{definition}\label{group.z_group}
\uses{group.cyclic,group.metacyclic,group.monomial,group.supersolvable}
A \textbf{Z-group} is a (finite) group all of whose Sylow subgroups are \hyperref[group.cyclic]{cyclic}. Such groups are \hyperref[group.metacyclic]{metacyclic}, \hyperref[group.supersolvable]{supersolvable} and \hyperref[group.monomial]{monomial}.

Every cyclic group is a Z-group, but the converse does not hold, as shown by <a href="{{url\_for('abstract.index')}}?Zgroup=yes&cyclic=no">these examples</a>.
\end{definition}
